**[1862, 12-19] Ms.A.1.2.31.166A**

HCW to WLG

“The Abolition of Slavery, & the perpetuity of the Republic, in its
essential principles & objects, are {u}fixed facts{/u} with me. But a
deeper baptism of blood awaits the Nation before it will do justice to
Negro [sic]. … {u}the Negro is the power of God & the Wisdom of God unto
salvation {/u}to this Republic.”


